1|"     (*) Charles VII of France, surnamed \"The Victorious,\" born"|FALSE
1|"     1403, died 1461."|FALSE
1|"     (+) Louis XI, son of the above, born 1423, died 1483."|FALSE
1|"But the scanty wisdom of man, on entering into an affair which looks"|FALSE
1|"well at first, cannot discern the poison that is hidden in it, as I have"|FALSE
1|"said above of hectic fevers. Therefore, if he who rules a principality"|FALSE
1|"cannot recognize evils until they are upon him, he is not truly wise;"|FALSE
1|"and this insight is given to few. And if the first disaster to the Roman"|FALSE
1|"Empire(*) should be examined, it will be found to have commenced only"|FALSE
1|"with the enlisting of the Goths; because from that time the vigour of"|FALSE
1|"the Roman Empire began to decline, and all that valour which had raised"|FALSE
1|"it passed away to others."|FALSE
1|"     (*) \"Many speakers to the House the other night in the"|FALSE
1|"     debate on the reduction of armaments seemed to show a most"|FALSE
1|"     lamentable ignorance of the conditions under which the"|FALSE
1|"     British Empire maintains its existence. When Mr Balfour"|FALSE
