1|"6. It has been a custom with princes, in order to hold their states"|FALSE
1|"more securely, to build fortresses that may serve as a bridle and bit"|FALSE
1|"to those who might design to work against them, and as a place of refuge"|FALSE
1|"from a first attack. I praise this system because it has been made use"|FALSE
1|"of formerly. Notwithstanding that, Messer Nicolo Vitelli in our times"|FALSE
1|"has been seen to demolish two fortresses in Citta di Castello so that he"|FALSE
1|"might keep that state; Guido Ubaldo, Duke of Urbino, on returning to"|FALSE
1|"his dominion, whence he had been driven by Cesare Borgia, razed to the"|FALSE
