1|"way they injure you in another. And this question can be reasoned thus:"|FALSE
1|"the prince who has more to fear from the people than from foreigners"|FALSE
1|"ought to build fortresses, but he who has more to fear from foreigners"|FALSE
1|"than from the people ought to leave them alone. The castle of Milan,"|FALSE
1|"built by Francesco Sforza, has made, and will make, more trouble for the"|FALSE
1|"house of Sforza than any other disorder in the state. For this reason"|FALSE
1|"the best possible fortress is--not to be hated by the people, because,"|FALSE
1|"although you may hold the fortresses, yet they will not save you if the"|FALSE
1|"people hate you, for there will never be wanting foreigners to assist"|FALSE
1|"a people who have taken arms against you. It has not been seen in our"|FALSE
